CONDOLENCES: Expresses the condolences of the House of Representatives on the death
of Allyce Trapp Alexander
1 A RESOLUTION
2 To express the condolences of the House of Representatives on the death of Allyce Trapp
3 Alexander.
4 WHEREAS, it is with immense sadness and profound regret that the House of
5 Representatives of the Legislature of Louisiana has learned of the passing, on September 27,
6 2025, of Allyce Trapp Alexander; and
7 WHEREAS, Allyce was born on January 6, 1994, in Houma, Louisiana, to Heinke
8 and Susan Trapp and was raised in a loving and supportive family; she graduated from
9 Vandebilt Catholic High School, where she participated in student council, tennis, and
10 volleyball and was voted best dressed for her ability to accessorize a uniform better than
11 anyone; as a teenager, she had the honor of being a maid of Mardi Gras in the Krewe of
12 Houmas; and
13 WHEREAS, Allyce moved to Baton Rouge in 2012 to attend Louisiana State
14 University and lived in the city for the remainder of her life; while at LSU, she joined Chi
15 Omega sorority and oversaw the election process for student government for one year; she
16 was a proud two-time graduate of the Manship School of Mass Communication and
17 particularly enjoyed spending a summer studying abroad in Germany; and
18 WHEREAS, Allyce found her calling while giving a speech at the Louisiana State
19 Capitol to raise awareness for dyslexia; she had learned to manage the learning disability
20 herself, becoming a student of history and an avid reader who often read two books at once;
21 and
