1 WHEREAS, Allyce established herself as a governmental affairs professional and
2 worked as a governmental affairs coordinator at Adams & Reese; in this role, she endeared
3 herself to everyone in the legislature with her smile and kindness, and as a Louisiana native,
4 she was always excited to go to work at the capitol; and
5 WHEREAS, outside of work, Allyce cherished spending time with her family,
6 friends, and colleagues; she loved fishing in the Gulf, wandering through museums, playing
7 with cats, and attending estate sales; she also enjoyed learning about British history,
8 especially the War of the Roses and the royal family, and savored a crisp glass of champagne
9 and a small raw oyster; and
10 WHEREAS, Allyce filled her beloved husband's days with joy; she was a natural
11 conversationalist who could talk to anyone about anything; she was a loyal and sweet friend
12 with trademark blonde bangs and an infectious energy that drew people to her; she sealed
13 the envelopes of her handwritten letters with a wax stamp, and she always gave her friends
14 and their children gifts on their birthdays; and
15 WHEREAS, Allyce Trapp Alexander is survived by her husband, Wilson Alexander;
16 parents, Heinke and Susan Trapp; brother, John Trapp; maternal grandmother, Ann Lirette;
17 and a host of aunts, uncles, and cousins; she was a smart, beautiful, elegant, and bright
18 young woman, and while she will be deeply missed, the legacy of her loving spirit shall live
19 on in the hearts and minds of those who were privileged to have known and loved her.
20 THEREFORE, BE IT RESOLVED that the House of Representatives of the
21 Legislature of Louisiana does hereby express heartfelt condolences on the death of Allyce
22 Trapp Alexander and does hereby extend sincere wishes that her family, friends, colleagues,
23 and loved ones find comfort in their shared memories of her beautiful life.
